<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05013n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05013n">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05013n"> 13(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> incest</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Why did not God create two couples instead of one? Adam and Eve&apos;s sons must have had children by their sisters. Surely an all-wise and all-good Creator would have prevented the cradle of the race from being stained with <mark>incest</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Creation Story] 24</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
